      <h1>Inspirations</h1>
      <div id="BeachInsp">
        <p>The Beach </p>
      </div>
      <div id="beachpicins"><img src="Images/beachinspirations.jpg" width="322" height="272"></div>
      <div id="beachinsinfo">
        <p>I love the beach. I first visited the beach when I was 19 and in Jamaica. I fell in love with it instantly. Then I fell in love with it again when I visited Port Aransas, Texas. </p>
        <p>Ever since these times I've felt a connection to the ocean. I express my love for the sand, waves, sky, and water in my paintings. </p>
      </div>
      <div id="loveinsp">Love, Flowers, &amp; Beauty</div>
      <div id="lovepics"><img src="Images/IMG_0582.jpg" width="279" height="376"><img src="Images/shawnme.jpg" width="267" height="376"><img src="Images/rose.jpg" width="267" height="376"></div>
      <div id="lovepicsinfo">
        <p>Flowers are a big inspiration for me. I love to paint different flowers. My favorites are roses, tulips, and sunflowers. Each type of flower has its own meaning but they all bloom and show beauty. </p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>The most driving inspiration is love. The love for beautiful things like a sunset or a city. But most importantly, the love I share with my boyfriend is the biggest of inspirations. </p>
      </div>
